201-209 East 86th Street, east of and adjoining the N.E. corner of Third Avenue. No. 205-209 will soon be torn down to make way for the National Bank of Yorkville. The Lyceum Theatre, No. 201 is the corner building.

August 2, 1927.

P. L. Sperr.

Third Avenue, east side, from 86th to 87th Streets; the Lyceum, 201 East 86th Street, is at the N.E. corner of 86th Street.
March 29, 1929.

P. L. Sperr.

Third Avenue, west side, north from 86th Street, showing 1530 Third Avenue, on the N. W. corner of 86th Street, a three-story frame house with a brick front.
1932.

J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York, Negative No. 240

204-208 East 86th Street, east of, adjoining, and at the S.E. corner of Third Avenue.
1932.

J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York.

165-171 East 86th Street, north side, west of Third Avenue. No. 167 is a three-story frame house with a brick front. No. 169 is the 86th Street entrance of Loew's Orpheum Theatre, which extends through to 87th Street.

1932.

The same.
